{"title_page": "List of Eastern Orthodox monasteries in the United States", "text_new": "<!-- Please don't add monasteries of non-chalkidon churches -->\nThe following is a list of [[Eastern Orthodox Christian]] [[monasticism|monasteries]] and [[skete]]s, both [[monk|male]] and [[nun|female]], in the United States of America.\n\n==Antiochian Orthodox Christian Archdiocese of North America==\n* [[St. Thekla Convent (Glenville, Pennsylvania)|St. Thekla Convent]], CLOSED.\n* [[St. Paul Skete (Grand Junction, Tennessee)|St. Paul Skete]], Grand Junction, Tennessee.  Female skete.  Superior: Mother Nektaria.\n<!--==Belarusian Council of Orthodox Churches in North America==-->\n* [[The Monastery of Our Lady and St. Laurence (Talahassee Creek, Colorado)|The Monastery of Our Lady and St. Laurence]], Canon City, Colorado. Prior: Father Theodore. www.ladyminster.com\n\n==Ecumenical Patriarchate institutions in America==\n\n===Stavropegial Monasteries===\n* [[Patriarchal Monastery of St. Irene Chrysovalantou (Astoria, New York)|Sacred Patriarchal and Stavropegial Monastery of St. Irene Chrysovalantou]], Astoria, New York. [http://www.stirene.org]. Abbot: Archimandrite [[Ierotheos]].\n* [[Holy Theotokos Monastery (North Fort Myers, Florida)|Holy Theotokos Monastery]], North Fort Myers, Florida.\n* [[Holy Patriarchal And Stavropegic Monastery Of The Entrance Of The Theotokos]], Malbis, Alabama. [https://www.patriarchate.org/holy-patriarchal-and-stavropegic-monastery-of-the-entrance-of-the-theotokos-in-alabama]\n\n===Greek Orthodox Archdiocese of America===\nThis archdiocese has had a small number of formerly Athonite monks who were given a blessing to start monasteries.  In recognition of this, any such spiritual father of a monastery will be listed.\n\n====Male====\n* [[St. Gregory Palamas Monastery (Hayesville, Ohio)|St. Gregory Palamas Monastery]], Hayesville, Ohio. Abbot, Archimandrite [[Joseph]]. Spiritual Father: Metropolitan [[Maximos of Pittsburgh]]. [http://sgpm.goarch.org/]\n* [[St. Anthony's Greek Orthodox Monastery (Florence, Arizona)|St. Anthony's Greek Orthodox Monastery]], Florence, Arizona.  Abbot: Archimandrite Paisios.  Spiritual Father: Elder [[Ephrem of Philotheou|Ephrem]]. [http://www.stanthonysmonastery.org]\n* [[Holy Archangels Greek Orthodox Monastery (Kendalia, Texas)|Holy Archangels Greek Orthodox Monastery]], Kendalia, Texas.  Archimandrite Dositheos.  Spiritual Father: Elder [[Ephrem of Philotheou|Ephrem]]. [http://www.holyarchangels.org/]\n* [[Panagia Vlahernon Greek Orthodox Monastery (Williston, Florida)|Panagia Vlahernon Greek Orthodox Monastery]], Williston, Florida.  Archimandrite Polycarp.  Spiritual Father: Elder [[Ephrem of Philotheou|Ephrem]] [http://www.panagiavlahernon.org/]\n* [[Holy Trinity Monastery Greek Orthodox Monastery (Smith Creek, Michigan)|Holy Trinity Monastery Greek Orthodox Monastery]], Smith Creek, Michigan.  Hieromonk Joseph.  Spiritual Father: Elder [[Ephrem of Philotheou|Ephrem]]\n* [[Panagia Pammakaristou Greek Orthodox Monastery (Lawsonville, North Carolina)|Panagia Pammakaristou Greek Orthodox Monastery]], Lawsonville, North Carolina.  Hieromonk Nektarios.  Spiritual Father: Elder [[Ephrem of Philotheou|Ephrem]]\n* [[St. Nektarios Greek Orthodox Monastery (Roscoe, New York)|St. Nektarios Greek Orthodox Monastery]], Roscoe, New York.  Archimandrite Joseph.  Spiritual Father: Elder [[Ephrem of Philotheou|Ephrem]]\n* [[Holy Transfiguration Greek Orthodox Monastery]], Harvard, Illinois. Father Akakios. Spiritual Father: [[Ephrem of Philotheou|Ephraim (Moraitis)]]\n\n====Female====\n* [[Entrance of the Mother of God into the Temple Skete (Hayesville, Ohio)|Entrance of the Mother of God into the Temple Skete]], Hayesville, Ohio.  Abbess Theadelphi.  Spiritual Father: Archimandrite [[Joseph]].\n* [[Nativity of the Theotokos Greek Orthodox Monastery (Saxonburg, Pennsylvania)|Nativity of the Theotokos Greek Orthodox Monastery]], Saxonburg, Pennsylvania.  Abbess Theophano.  Spiritual Father